Think a stickman versus a human. A proper human face portrait is something that takes into account all the details of the face, you have to take into account the shape of the skull, the eyes, the nose, the hairstyle and loads of other stuff in order for it to be a drawing of someones face, a good one, intead of a kid trying to draw just a circle head, maybe a few squigly lines and call it a day. So instead, if you want to draw it properly, you go on and you firstly refine the head shape you want, make sure everything stays up to the basics, then you inspect what exactly it is you want to do. Consider, think and apply the best way to do it, plan out your shapes and the way you want to do them to look, make that human drawing something someone can look at and say "Yep, thats a drawing of a human", instead of "Yep, this doesn't look like a human but I know its meant to be one."
